# UI Refactoring Walkthrough (Phase 6)

This document details the refactoring of the [SettingsPage](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/SettingsPage.xaml.cs#10-196) to align with the iOS 26 design language, specifically implementing a "Grouped List" style.

## 1. Goal
Replace the manual card-based layout in [SettingsPage.xaml](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/SettingsPage.xaml) with a standardized, reusable `iOS26.SettingsGroup` and `iOS26.SettingsItem` style system to achieve a cleaner, more native-feeling iOS aesthetics.

## 2. Changes

### New Styles ([Styles/iOS26.xaml](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Styles/iOS26.xaml))
Added the following styles to standardizes the look of settings:
-   **`iOS26.SettingsSectionHeader`**: Sticky-like headers for sections (e.g., "GAME ENVIRONMENT").
-   **`iOS26.SettingsGroup`**: The container for a group of settings, featuring a backdrop, corner radius, and shadow.
-   **`iOS26.SettingsItem`**: The base style for individual rows, ensuring consistent height, padding, and separators.
-   **`iOS26.SettingsItem.Title`** & **`iOS26.SettingsItem.Value`**: Typography styles for consistent text rendering.

### Settings Page Refactoring ([SettingsPage.xaml](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/SettingsPage.xaml))
-   **Removed**: Manual `Border` cards with hardcoded colors and shadows.
-   **Implemented**:
    -   **Game Environment**: Game Path selection and Version Isolation toggle using the new styles.
    -   **Java Settings**: Java Path browsing and Auto-Detect button integrated into clickable setting rows.
    -   **Memory Allocation**: Segmented control for mode selection and a slider row for memory amount.
    -   **Accounts**: List of accounts and "Add Account" actions within a settings group.
    -   **General**: Language selection and Update check.

### Interaction Logic
-   Retained all existing functionality (Path browsing, Auto-search, Memory slider).
-   Switched from [Button](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/VersionSettingsDialog.xaml.cs#39-70) wrappers to `Border` with `MouseLeftButtonDown` events for cleaner XAML structure and better hit-testing on "transparent" backgrounds inside the list.

## 3. Verification

### Visual Inspection
-   **Headers**: Section headers are uppercase (manually formatted) and distinct.
-   **Groups**: Settings are grouped in rounded "islands" typical of iOS settings.
-   **Rows**: Each row has consistent height and alignment.
-   **Separators**: Implicitly handled (currently by border bottom on items, last item border removal can be polished later if needed, but currently looks acceptable).

### Functional Testing
-   **Clickability**: "Game Path", "Java Runtime", and "Auto-Detect Java" rows are clickable and trigger their respective logic.
-   **Toggles & Sliders**: Toggle switches and the Memory Slider work as expected within the new layout.
-   **Data Binding**: Path texts and version info update correctly when changed.

